						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Rājarāja I Year 24: 1009 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This incomplete inscription, which is engraved in late characters, begins with the usual <hi rend="italic">meykīrtti</hi> of the ruler, <hi rend="italic">Tirumagaḷ-pōla</hi> etc., of the above king. It seems to record some dealing between two persons, Vēḷmuttaraiyaṉ and Perumāṉ Tiruveṇṇāvallāṉ Mullaiarai [Peru]muttaraiyaṉ. Other details are lost.</p>						

